@huangyuyu0426 
Basically, you can create the masks in an image editing software if you want them to be precise i.e. removing an object from an image. In which you have to make sure that the mask covers the entire object in the image. We use Adobe Photoshop for that matter.
If you only need to test the model with some random mask, then you can either create them in python or use the referenced datasets. But please note that we use binary masks in our model. That means you need to save mask images in `.png` format as I have explained here: https://github.com/knazeri/edge-connect/issues/37#issuecomment-458182472
